"I like the taste of hands" - Gordie, Current bite quarantine resident âœ‹ğŸ» If a kitty at the shelter bites someone and draws blood, they have to be quarantined (basically kitty time out) for ten days as per county regulations. Essentially, it just allows us to make sure that they don't have rabies and haven't passed it to whoever they bit. Once their time out is over, they move back upstairs and are available for adoption again! Most of the cats who bite in the shelter are nice cats who are startled or scared in the moment. We don't have any problems finding them their purrfect new homes once they're available for adoption again!
@krikripdx He would love my delicious hand!!!
Why shame him? You try and make it sound cute but youâ€™re now probably turning away more potential folks from adopting a â€œbadâ€ cat.

Poor Gordie. I can only imagine how much time my old kitty would have spent in quarantine if sheâ€™d ended up in a shelter as an adult. Fortunately we had her from 8 wks old until she passed at 15. â¤ï¸
What I have never understood is why quarantine (in general) when they have had and are current on rabies vaccine?

@jpanday It certainly isn't my intention to turn people away from adopting him. I just wanted to explain about the bite quarantine process and how we handle bites at the shelter. I'm sure he won't have any problems being adopted as soon as he's available!

@acdgirl That's a good question! It's one of those old county laws that we have to follow. The county calls in the middle of and after the quarantine is over to check on the status of both the cat and the human involved. They actually just changed the rules in our county - it used to be that if a cat bit three times at the shelter and drew blood every time that we wouldn't be able to adopt them out. We had to transfer them out of the county to another shelter where the rules were different so they could find a home. Thankfully they changed the rule last year, so now there isn't a limit.
@reggiedoodle9 Gordie is such a sweet cat! My cats wouldn't do well with bite restrictions either. Thank goodness you don't have to quarantine them at home!
Poor Gordie! I'd bite people that chop off my danglers too!

@catadoptpdx all cats bite!! Just caution the family who might be interested in him.. problem solved!! Let's not make such small things into such a big deal.. after all its a young playful cat. .That's all.. Please don't cage him for 10 days.. that'll only make it worse in my opinion
